  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The financial_transaction_metrics view (source: financial_transactions) has dimensions: transaction_date, department, gl_category, fiscal_quarter. Measures: total_transactions, total_revenue_usd, total_cogs_usd, total_opex_usd, total_capex_usd. The budget_variance_metrics view (source: budget_snapshots) has dimensions: snapshot_date, department, budget_status. Measures: total_budgeted_usd, total_actual_usd, total_variance_usd, avg_variance_pct, critical_overrun_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. cost_center_id, cost_center_name).",
